{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_5","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc 'rg -n \"WakeTask|wake task|alarm|task|opportunity|MVP|core phase|core\" .workflow/iphone-app-factory kitty-specs/waketask-iphone-app-01KRK02R | head -n 200'","aggregated_output":"kitty-specs/waketask-iphone-app-01KRK02R/meta.json:3:  \"friendly_name\": \"waketask iphone app\",\nkitty-specs/waketask-iphone-app-01KRK02R/meta.json:6:  \"mission_slug\": \"waketask-iphone-app-01KRK02R\",\nkitty-specs/waketask-iphone-app-01KRK02R/meta.json:8:  \"slug\": \"waketask-iphone-app-01KRK02R\",\nkitty-specs/waketask-iphone-app-01KRK02R/tasks/README.md:8:tasks/\nkitty-specs/waketask-iphone-app-01KRK02R/tasks/README.md:15:All WP files are stored flat in `tasks/`. Status is tracked in `status.events.jsonl`, not in WP frontmatter.\nkitty-specs/waketask-iphone-app-01KRK02R/tasks/README.md:29:subtasks:\nkitty-specs/waketask-iphone-app-01KRK02R/tasks/README.md:39:    action: \"Prompt generated via /spec-kitty.tasks\"\nkitty-specs/waketask-iphone-app-01KRK02R/tasks/README.md:50:Use `spec-kitty agent tasks move-task` to change WP status:\nkitty-specs/waketask-iphone-app-01KRK02R/tasks/README.md:53:spec-kitty agent tasks move-task <WPID> --to <lane>\nkitty-specs/waketask-iphone-app-01KRK02R/tasks/README.md:58:spec-kitty agent tasks move-task WP01 --to doing\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/boilerplate-contract.json:3:  \"appDir\": \"apps/waketask-iphone\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:1:# ADR: WakeTask on SwiftAIBoilerplatePro\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:9:WakeTask will be implemented by extending `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro` modules and composition boundaries, with no foundational module removals in MVP.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:16:5. `Packages/Storage`: retain for persistent reliability timeline and alarm state.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:19:8. `Packages/AI`: retain unchanged; restricted to non-alarm-critical UX.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:28:- Preserves App Store 4.3 differentiation by focusing changes on WakeTask-specific behavior (two-phase wake model, fallback safety rails, reliability telemetry) rather than generic foundation rewrites.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:39:If a module is removed or replaced without preserving differentiated WakeTask behavior:\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:40:- Risk of clone-like implementation increases if UX degrades into generic alarm/paywall templates.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:46:- Smallest-surface architecture bias is accepted for MVP speed and reduced regression area.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:51:- Negative: some future extensibility is deferred to post-MVP ADRs.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:1:# WakeTask Architecture\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:4:Build WakeTask as an extension of `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro` with no foundational rewrites, preserving strict Swift 6 concurrency, CI quality gates, and App Store differentiation through the two-phase wake model.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:9:3. Feature packages implement WakeTask domain flows behind protocol boundaries owned by `Packages/Core`.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:10:4. iOS app target and UI tests validate end-to-end alarm, mission, fallback, and wake-check flows.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:14:  - Keep as root project; add WakeTask feature targets/schemes only as needed.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:16:  - Keep as source of bundle id/environment toggles (`com.keen.waketask`) and build flags.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:18:  - Owns domain models/protocols for alarms, mission chain, wake-check schedule, reliability timeline, and context profile selection.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:20:  - Reused for remote config/pricing copy fetches and optional telemetry upload; no alarm-critical behavior depends on network availability.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:22:  - Persists per-alarm reliability telemetry fields (`alarm_scheduled_at`, `alarm_fired_at`, `dismissed_at`, `wake_check_results`, `fallback_used`, `profile_used`) and mission/profile configuration.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:26:  - Retained for transparent paywall and entitlement checks; monetization messaging kept outside alarm-critical interaction steps.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:28:  - Retained for non-critical assistant/personalization surfaces only; never required for alarm firing, dismissal, fallback, or wake verification.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:30:  - Hosts alarm defaults, strictness profiles (weekday/weekend/travel), permission recovery affordances, and tone/policy options.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:38:## WakeTask Feature Slices\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:40:- Configure alarm + mission chain.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:44:- Fire alarm locally.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:50:- Escalate via re-alarm on missed/failed checks.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:59:2. `FeatureSettings` and WakeTask feature UIs depend on `Core` protocols and DesignSystem.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:65:- Isolate alarm-state mutation behind actor-backed services.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:78:- No sleep-stage analytics platform, social wake community, or wearable-required core logic in MVP.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-kitty.json:1:{\"result\": \"success\", \"mission_slug\": \"waketask-iphone-app-01KRK02R\", \"mission_number\": null, \"mission_id\": \"01KRK02R27K7320Z511QDBQSMA\", \"mission_type\": \"software-dev\", \"slug\": \"waketask-iphone-app-01KRK02R\", \"friendly_name\": \"waketask iphone app\", \"feature_dir\": \"/home/daytona/workspace/kitty-specs/waketask-iphone-app-01KRK02R\", \"spec_file\": \"/home/daytona/workspace/kitty-specs/waketask-iphone-app-01KRK02R/spec.md\", \"meta_file\": \"/home/daytona/workspace/kitty-specs/waketask-iphone-app-01KRK02R/meta.json\", \"created_at\": \"2026-05-14T10:21:24.975945+00:00\", \"created_files\": [\"/home/daytona/workspace/kitty-specs/waketask-iphone-app-01KRK02R/spec.md\", \"/home/daytona/workspace/kitty-specs/waketask-iphone-app-01KRK02R/meta.json\", \"/home/daytona/workspace/kitty-specs/waketask-iphone-app-01KRK02R/tasks/README.md\"], \"write_mode\": \"update_existing_files\", \"next_step\": \"Read then update spec_file/meta_file; do not recreate with blind write.\", \"current_branch\": \"fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS\", \"CURRENT_BRANCH\": \"fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS\", \"target_branch\": \"fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS\", \"base_branch\": \"fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS\", \"TARGET_BRANCH\": \"fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS\", \"BASE_BRANCH\": \"fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS\", \"planning_base_branch\": \"fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS\", \"PLANNING_BASE_BRANCH\": \"fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS\", \"merge_target_branch\": \"fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS\", \"MERGE_TARGET_BRANCH\": \"fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS\", \"EXPECTED_TARGET_BRANCH\": \"fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS\", \"EXPECTED_BASE_BRANCH\": \"fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS\", \"branch_matches_target\": true, \"BRANCH_MATCHES_TARGET\": true, \"branch_strategy_summary\": \"Current branch at workflow start: fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS. Planning/base branch for this feature: fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS. Completed changes must merge into fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS.\", \"runtime_vars\": {\"now_utc_iso\": \"2026-05-14T10:21:25Z\", \"current_branch\": \"fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS\", \"target_branch\": \"fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS\", \"base_branch\": \"fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS\", \"planning_base_branch\": \"fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS\", \"merge_target_branch\": \"fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS\", \"branch_matches_target\": true, \"branch_strategy_summary\": \"Current branch at workflow start: fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS. Planning/base branch for this feature: fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS. Completed changes must merge into fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS.\"}, \"NOW_UTC_ISO\": \"2026-05-14T10:21:25Z\", \"branch_context\": {\"current_branch\": \"fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS\", \"target_branch\": \"fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS\", \"base_branch\": \"fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS\", \"planning_base_branch\": \"fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS\", \"merge_target_branch\": \"fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS\", \"expected_checkout_branch\": \"fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS\", \"matches_target\": true, \"branch_strategy_summary\": \"Current branch at workflow start: fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS. Planning/base branch for this feature: fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS. Completed changes must merge into fabro/run/01KRJY9F9PKV1P01YH46A57WTS.\"}, \"spec_kitty_version\": \"3.1.8\"}\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-red-team.md:19:- Competitive analysis is specific (Alarmy, Challenges Alarm Clock, Instant Wake Up, Alarm Clock for Me, Sleep Cycle/Pillow) and maps strengths/weaknesses to opportunity areas.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-red-team.md:30:- Acceptance criteria define testable behavior for each core mission type and for fallback behavior.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-red-team.md:43:- Core product loop (mission-gated dismissal + post-dismiss wake verification + reliability log) is clearly differentiated from commodity alarm templates.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-red-team.md:48:- Differentiation depends on execution quality of wake-check escalation and reliability timeline UX; weak implementation could collapse into a mission-alarm clone.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-red-team.md:56:- Quality bar forbidden list reinforces no rebuild of core platform modules without ADR approval.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md:4:App: WakeTask (`com.keen.waketask`)\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md:9:- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/opportunity-matrix.json`\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md:14:Note on candidate specs: the workspace did not contain auditable per-model candidate files (Gemini/Claude/Kimi/DeepSeek). Consensus was therefore built from the available evidence synthesis, opportunity ranking, critique gap list, and quality bar constraints.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md:18:- Keep WakeTask positioned as a sustained wakefulness product, not a generic alarm clone.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md:19:- Preserve the two-phase model as core differentiation:\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md:26:- Make reliability visible to users via per-alarm telemetry and morning timeline log.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md:3:- [ ] Product scope lock: implementation matches `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md` MVP scope and excludes listed non-goals.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md:12:- [ ] Reliability telemetry persisted per alarm with required fields:\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md:13:  - `alarm_scheduled_at`\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md:14:  - `alarm_fired_at`\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md:19:- [ ] Morning reliability log UI displays telemetry timeline for each alarm event.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md:21:- [ ] Permission gating implemented: notifications pre-alarm, camera only for scan mission, denial recovery path present.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:3:Product: WakeTask (`com.keen.waketask`)\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:5:WakeTask is a wake-accountability iPhone app focused on sustained wakefulness, not just alarm dismissal. The core model is a two-phase wake flow: mission-gated dismissal followed by post-dismiss wake verification.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:9:- Users report autopilot alarm dismissal and relapse sleep within minutes.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:10:- Reliability trust is fragile; users keep backup alarms due to fear of missed firing or mission failure loops.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:11:- Competitive demand is validated for mission alarms, but incumbents are frequently criticized for ad clutter, pricing shock, and brittle flows.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:21:1. Setup and first alarm\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:23:- User creates an alarm and selects a mission chain.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:34:- Missed/failed check triggers escalating re-alarm behavior.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:39:- User sees event timeline and fallback usage for each alarm.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:44:## MVP Scope\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:47:- Mission-gated alarm dismissal with chain support (math, memory, motion, scan).\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:51:- Per-alarm reliability log with user-visible timeline fields.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:98:- Any missed/failed check triggers escalation re-alarm.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:106:4. Reliability telemetry fields (per alarm)\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:107:- Required: `alarm_scheduled_at`, `alarm_fired_at`, `dismissed_at`, `wake_check_results`, `fallback_used`, `profile_used`.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:111:- Notifications requested before first active alarm enablement.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:129:- Explorer taps every reachable enabled control in MVP flows with bounded-depth traversal.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md:14:- Product focus: anti-bypass wake accountability, not generic alarm utility.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md:15:- MVP shape: mission-gated dismissal + post-dismiss wake checks + reliability log.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md:42:- Generic \"mission alarm\" feature list without unique interaction model.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md:43:- Reused boilerplate visuals/copy without WakeTask-specific wake-accountability mechanics.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md:45:- Near-identical onboarding/feature naming to incumbent alarm apps.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md:49:- User-visible reliability proof surface (morning log) as core product behavior.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md:74:- Vague: \"WakeTask ensures users are awake.\"\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md:77:  - Verifiable rewrite: \"For each alarm, write telemetry fields `{alarm_scheduled_at, alarm_fired_at, dismiss_at, checks_completed, fallback_used}` and show in morning log.\"\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/opportunity-matrix.json:8:        \"Competitor set emphasizes dismissal tasks but weak sustained wake verification.\"\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/opportunity-matrix.json:10:      \"user_pain\": \"Users can complete or dismiss alarms while half-asleep and relapse into sleep minutes later.\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/opportunity-matrix.json:11:      \"mvp_feature\": \"Mandatory wake-check sequence at configurable intervals after initial dismissal, with escalating re-alarm if missed.\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/opportunity-matrix.json:12:      \"differentiation\": \"Optimizes for sustained wakefulness outcome rather than alarm-stop event.\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/opportunity-matrix.json:30:        \"Users maintain backup alarms due to fear of app failure.\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/opportunity-matrix.json:32:        \"Research indicates trust collapses quickly after a single missed alarm incident.\"\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/opportunity-matrix.json:34:      \"user_pain\": \"Users cannot verify whether alarm protections are actually ready before sleep.\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/opportunity-matrix.json:44:        \"Demand exists for hard alarms that remain usable across contexts.\"\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/opportunity-matrix.json:46:      \"user_pain\": \"Strict alarm systems become brittle outside normal home routine.\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/opportunity-matrix.json:59:      \"mvp_feature\": \"Distraction-minimal alarm screens, large controls, and transparent pricing/paywall messaging.\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md:1:# WakeTask Research Synthesis\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md:6:- **Target user**: iPhone users (students, shift workers, professionals, ADHD-leaning routine strugglers, heavy sleepers) who regularly snooze, dismiss alarms in sleep inertia, and return to sleep.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md:7:- Urgent problem: default alarm behaviors optimize for sound delivery, not sustained wakefulness; users need a reliable system that ensures they are physically and cognitively awake after alarm dismissal.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md:8:- Market signal: App Store mission-alarm leaders show strong demand, while Reddit users describe active switching due to ad bloat, bypass loopholes, and reliability mistrust.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md:13:2. \"After alarm dismissal, keep me awake long enough to avoid relapse sleep.\"\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md:20:- Evidence summary: users report they can complete tasks unconsciously and \"have no memory,\" then return to bed.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md:24:- Evidence summary: App Store and Reddit evidence shows users keep backups when alarms crash, background execution fails, or mission completion loops break.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md:52:## Feature opportunity matrix\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md:56:- Differentiation: optimize for \"still awake,\" not merely \"alarm dismissed.\"\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md:64:- User pain: no trust that alarm stack actually executed as intended.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md:65:- Opportunity: visible morning log (alarm fired time, dismiss time, fallback path used).\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md:69:- User pain: home-anchored tasks break while traveling.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md:79:WakeTask is a focused wake-accountability product, not a clone alarm utility. The core thesis is: **\"reliability-verified, anti-bypass wake completion with post-dismissal accountability.\"**\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md:82:- Distinct outcome metric: sustained wakefulness, not alarm playback.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md:89:- Large tap targets, low-choice alarm screens, clear hierarchy of urgent actions.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md:90:- Visual language: calm high-contrast morning palette; avoid gamified noise during alarm-critical state.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md:94:## MVP scope and non-goals\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md:95:### MVP scope\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md:96:- Task-gated alarms with chained missions (math/memory/motion/scan).\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md:99:- Reliability log for each alarm event.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-evidence-gate.json:10:    \".workflow/iphone-app-factory/opportunity-matrix.json\"\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:9:        \"raw\": \"Evaluate whether this iPhone App Factory prompt suite is strong enough for overnight agentic app generation.\\n\\nPrompt registry:\\n{{prompt_registry}}\\n\\nGolden cases:\\n{{golden_cases}}\\n\\nRepresentative prompts:\\nSPEC_CONSENSUS:\\n{{spec_consensus}}\\n\\nARCHITECTURE:\\n{{architecture_consensus}}\\n\\nIMPLEMENT_INTEGRATION:\\n{{implement_integration}}\\n\\nAI_UI_EXPLORER:\\n{{ai_ui_explorer}}\\n\\nFINAL_CONSENSUS:\\n{{final_consensus}}\\n\\nReturn valid JSON only, no markdown fences:\\n{\\\"verdict\\\":\\\"APPROVE\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.0,\\\"covered\\\":[\\\"spec_lab\\\",\\\"boilerplate_reuse\\\",\\\"ios_quality\\\",\\\"appium_qa\\\",\\\"mobbin_safety\\\",\\\"release_hardening\\\"],\\\"gaps\\\":[]}\\n\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:10:        \"label\": \"Evaluate whether this iPhone App Factory prompt suite is strong enough for overnight agentic app generation.\\n\\nPrompt registry:\\n{{prompt_registry}}\\n\\nGolden cases:\\n{{golden_cases}}\\n\\nRepresentative prompts:\\nSPEC_CONSENSUS:\\n{{spec_consensus}}\\n\\nARCHITECTURE:\\n{{architecture_consensus}}\\n\\nIMPLEMENT_INTEGRATION:\\n{{implement_integration}}\\n\\nAI_UI_EXPLORER:\\n{{ai_ui_explorer}}\\n\\nFINAL_CONSENSUS:\\n{{final_consensus}}\\n\\nReturn valid JSON only, no markdown fences:\\n{\\\"verdict\\\":\\\"APPROVE\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.0,\\\"covered\\\":[\\\"spec_lab\\\",\\\"boilerplate_reuse\\\",\\\"ios_quality\\\",\\\"appium_qa\\\",\\\"mobbin_safety\\\",\\\"release_hardening\\\"],\\\"gaps\\\":[]}\\n\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:13:          \"score\": 0,\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:48:          \"namedScores\": {},\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:49:          \"namedScoresCount\": {},\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:50:          \"namedScoreWeights\": {},\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:61:          \"score\": 0,\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:63:          \"namedScores\": {},\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:74:              \"score\": 0,\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:95:              \"score\": 0,\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:108:                \"renderedGradingPrompt\": \"[{\\\"role\\\":\\\"system\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"You are grading output according to a user-specified rubric. If the statement in the rubric is true, then the output passes the test. You respond with a JSON object with this structure: {reason: string, pass: boolean, score: number}\\\\n\\\\nExamples:\\\\n\\\\n<Output>Hello world</Output>\\\\n<Rubric>Content contains a greeting</Rubric>\\\\n{\\\\\\\"reason\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"the content contains the word 'Hello'\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"pass\\\\\\\": true, \\\\\\\"score\\\\\\\": 1.0}\\\\n\\\\n<Output>Avast ye swabs, repel the invaders!</Output>\\\\n<Rubric>Does not speak like a pirate</Rubric>\\\\n{\\\\\\\"reason\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"'avast ye' is a common pirate term\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"pass\\\\\\\": false, \\\\\\\"score\\\\\\\": 0.0}\\\"},{\\\"role\\\":\\\"user\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"<Output>\\\\n# Evaluation: iPhone App Factory Prompt Suite\\\\n\\\\n## Overall Assessment: **STRONG BUT WITH CRITICAL GAPS** (7.2/10)\\\\n\\\\nThis is a well-architected prompt suite with excellent structural discipline, but it has **three blocking vulnerabilities** for overnight agentic execution.\\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n\\\\n## Strengths ✅\\\\n\\\\n| Category | Evidence |\\\\n|----------|----------|\\\\n| **Workflow coherence** | Clear stage progression (research → spec → architecture → implementation → review → release) |\\\\n| **Spec lab rigor** | Independent candidates + adversarial critique + red team + consensus pattern is sound |\\\\n| **Boilerplate enforcement** | Multiple checkpoints (spec, architecture, implementation, review) bias toward reuse |\\\\n| **Quality gates** | Explicit xcodebuild, SwiftLint, SwiftFormat, Qlty, Appium requirements |\\\\n| **Verdict discipline** | Binary APPROVED/REJECTED verdicts with blocking rules prevent ambiguous handoffs |\\\\n| **Secret handling intent** | \\\\\\\"Never print environment variables\\\\\\\" appears 6+ times |\\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n\\\\n## Critical Gaps ❌\\\\n\\\\n### 1. **Secret Handling is Underspecified** (BLOCKING)\\\\n\\\\n**Problem:**\\\\n- `research-design-patterns.md` must_include lists `MOBBIN_EMAIL`, `MOBBIN_PASSWORD` but no prompt shows *how* to use them safely\\\\n- `implement-foundation.md` mentions \\\\\\\"secrets\\\\\\\" but doesn't specify injection mechanism\\\\n- No prompt explicitly forbids `os.environ.dump()`, `print(os.environ)`, or credential logging in agent outputs\\\\n- No prompt specifies redaction rules for CI logs\\\\n\\\\n**Risk:** Overnight agent could leak credentials to stdout/logs during research or implementation phases.\\\\n\\\\n**Required fix:**\\\\n```yaml\\\\nmust_include: [\\\\n  \\\\\\\"never print environment variables\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"use getenv() with redaction wrapper\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"credential verification: true/false only\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"no credential values in logs or reports\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"sanitize all JSON outputs for secrets\\\\\\\"\\\\n]\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\n### 2. **Appium/XCUITest Evidence is Optional** (BLOCKING FOR OVERNIGHT)\\\\n\\\\n**Problem:**\\\\n- `ai-ui-explorer.md` says \\\\\\\"Do not mark the pass complete unless a real simulator/Appium run happened, **unless the workflow explicitly allows macOS deferral**\\\\\\\"\\\\n- `final-consensus.md` says \\\\\\\"If macOS/Xcode or Appium evidence is missing **and not explicitly deferred**, reject\\\\\\\"\\\\n- No prompt defines what \\\\\\\"explicitly deferred\\\\\\\" means or under what conditions it's acceptable\\\\n- Overnight execution on headless CI likely cannot run iOS simulator → creates escape hatch for skipping QA\\\\n\\\\n**Risk:** Agent defers Appium, skips real device testing, ships untested app.\\\\n\\\\n**Required fix:**\\\\n```yaml\\\\n# In final-consensus.md\\\\nRules:\\\\n  - Appium deferral only allowed if:\\\\n    1. Workflow input explicitly sets \\\\\\\"defer_appium: true\\\\\\\"\\\\n    2. A blocking issue prevents simulator setup (documented)\\\\n</Output>\\\\n<Rubric>\\\\nThe prompt suite should make quality reproducible across prompt registry, golden cases, adversarial review, deterministic gates, and final release criteria.\\\\n</Rubric>\\\"}]\"\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:115:        \"namedScores\": {},\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:117:          \"raw\": \"Evaluate whether this iPhone App Factory prompt suite is strong enough for overnight agentic app generation.\\n\\nPrompt registry:\\n{\\n  \\\"workflow\\\": \\\"iphone-app-factory\\\",\\n  \\\"dataset_version\\\": \\\"iphone-app-factory-prompts-v1\\\",\\n  \\\"rubric_version\\\": \\\"iphone-app-factory-prompt-rubric-v1\\\",\\n  \\\"prompts\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/research-app-store.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"research\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"App Store\\\", \\\"reviews\\\", \\\"evidence quality\\\", \\\"do not invent\\\", \\\"never print environment variables\\\", \\\"environment dump commands\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/research-reddit.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"research\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"Reddit\\\", \\\"source links\\\", \\\"do not fabricate\\\", \\\"never print environment variables\\\", \\\"environment dump commands\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/research-competitors.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"research\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"competitor\\\", \\\"positioning\\\", \\\"evidence quality\\\", \\\"never print environment variables\\\", \\\"environment dump commands\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/research-design-patterns.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"design\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"Mobbin\\\", \\\"MOBBIN_EMAIL\\\", \\\"MOBBIN_PASSWORD\\\", \\\"not clone\\\", \\\"never print environment variables\\\", \\\"environment dump commands\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/synthesize-research.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"synthesis\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"jobs-to-be-done\\\", \\\"differentiation\\\", \\\"opportunity-matrix.json\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/spec-candidate.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"spec\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"independent\\\", \\\"Definition of Done\\\", \\\"Appium\\\", \\\"SwiftAIBoilerplatePro\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"spec-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"adversarial\\\", \\\"contradictions\\\", \\\"testability gaps\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"spec\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"Research Evidence\\\", \\\"Boilerplate Reuse\\\", \\\"Appium Exploratory QA\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/spec-red-team.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"spec-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"VERDICT: APPROVED\\\", \\\"VERDICT: REJECTED\\\", \\\"release criteria\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/architecture-candidate.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"architecture\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"extends SwiftAIBoilerplatePro\\\", \\\"CompositionRoot\\\", \\\"Appium\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/architecture-consensus.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"architecture\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"architecture.md\\\", \\\"adr.md\\\", \\\"Packages/Core\\\", \\\"CompositionRoot\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/boilerplate-setup.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"implementation\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"do not recreate\\\", \\\"AGENTS.md\\\", \\\"DISTRIBUTION_README.md\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/implement-foundation.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"implementation\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"BrandConfig\\\", \\\"secrets\\\", \\\"Appium exploratory\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/implement-core.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"implementation\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"repositories\\\", \\\"ViewModel\\\", \\\"unit tests\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/implement-interface.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"implementation\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"DesignSystem\\\", \\\"accessibility\\\", \\\"actual app experience\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/implement-integration.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"implementation\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"xcodebuild\\\", \\\"SwiftLint\\\", \\\"SwiftFormat\\\", \\\"Appium\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/verify-phase.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"verify\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"independently verify\\\", \\\"boilerplate conventions\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-implementation-correctness.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"code-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"correctness\\\", \\\"spec.md\\\", \\\"blocking\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-implementation-tests.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"code-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"tests\\\", \\\"xcodebuild\\\", \\\"Appium\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-implementation-security.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"code-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"security\\\", \\\"privacy\\\", \\\"secrets\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-implementation-boilerplate.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"code-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"SwiftAIBoilerplatePro\\\", \\\"boilerplate\\\", \\\"unnecessary rebuild\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-implementation-consensus.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"code-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"implementation-consensus.md\\\", \\\"VERDICT: APPROVED\\\", \\\"VERDICT: REJECTED\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/simplification.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"simplify\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"split Swift files\\\", \\\"400 lines\\\", \\\"do not remove quality gates\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/ai-ui-explorer.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"qa\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"tap every reachable\\\", \\\"reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json\\\", \\\"crashes\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/app-store-hardening.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"release\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"SwiftAI\\\", \\\"Boilerplate\\\", \\\"release strings audit: PASS\\\", \\\"Privacy\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-product-fidelity.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"spec.md\\\", \\\"research synthesis\\\", \\\"template-like\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-ios-architecture.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"architecture.md\\\", \\\"Swift 6\\\", \\\"CompositionRoot\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-security-privacy.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"Security\\\", \\\"Privacy\\\", \\\"hardcoded secrets\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-code-quality.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"SwiftLint\\\", \\\"SwiftFormat\\\", \\\"Qlty\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-release-readiness.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"iOS CI report\\\", \\\"TestFlight\\\", \\\"macOS/Xcode\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-qa-evidence.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"Appium\\\", \\\"button tap coverage\\\", \\\"crashes\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/final-consensus.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"VERDICT: APPROVED\\\", \\\"VERDICT: REJECTED\\\", \\\"boilerplate\\\"]\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n\\nGolden cases:\\n{\\\"id\\\":\\\"spec-lab\\\",\\\"input\\\":\\\"The spec lab prompts should force independent candidates, adversarial critique, consensus, red team, and a testable Definition of Done.\\\",\\\"expected_quality\\\":[\\\"independent candidates\\\",\\\"adversarial critique\\\",\\\"consensus merge\\\",\\\"red team verdict\\\",\\\"testable Definition of Done\\\"]}\\n{\\\"id\\\":\\\"boilerplate-first\\\",\\\"input\\\":\\\"Implementation prompts should bias agents to extend SwiftAIBoilerplatePro instead of rebuilding auth, payments, AI, storage, networking, localization, settings, or design system.\\\",\\\"expected_quality\\\":[\\\"boilerplate reuse\\\",\\\"module boundaries\\\",\\\"CompositionRoot\\\",\\\"no platform rewrite\\\",\\\"App Store 4.3 awareness\\\"]}\\n{\\\"id\\\":\\\"ios-qa\\\",\\\"input\\\":\\\"Quality prompts should require macOS Xcode evidence, strict Swift lint/format/static checks, sensitive-value scanning, Appium/XCUITest exploratory clicking, and release string audits.\\\",\\\"expected_quality\\\":[\\\"xcodebuild build/test\\\",\\\"SwiftLint\\\",\\\"SwiftFormat\\\",\\\"Qlty\\\",\\\"sensitive scan\\\",\\\"Appium exploratory tapping\\\",\\\"release string audit\\\"]}\\n{\\\"id\\\":\\\"mobbin-safe\\\",\\\"input\\\":\\\"Design research prompts may use Mobbin credential env vars but should not leak credentials, clone screens, or copy assets.\\\",\\\"expected_quality\\\":[\\\"credential env vars\\\",\\\"no secret logging\\\",\\\"pattern abstraction\\\",\\\"no cloning\\\",\\\"Apple HIG or DesignSystem cross-check\\\"]}\\n\\nRepresentative prompts:\\nSPEC_CONSENSUS:\\n# Spec Consensus\\n\\nRead:\\n\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/opportunity-matrix.json`\\n- all spec candidate outputs in context\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/quality-bar.json`\\n\\nMerge the strongest ideas into one buildable spec.\\n\\nWrite:\\n\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md`\\n\\n`spec.md` must include these section headings exactly:\\n\\n- `# Product Spec`\\n- `## Research Evidence`\\n- `## User Journeys`\\n- `## MVP Scope`\\n- `## Boilerplate Reuse`\\n- `## Design Direction`\\n- `## Acceptance Criteria`\\n- `## Appium Exploratory QA`\\n- `## App Store Readiness`\\n- `## Definition of Done`\\n\\nThe Definition of Done must be checklist-based and testable.\\n\\nARCHITECTURE:\\n# Architecture And ADR Consensus\\n\\nRead:\\n\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md`\\n- all architecture candidates in context\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/quality-bar.json`\\n\\nWrite:\\n\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md`\\n\\nThe architecture must explicitly map the product to SwiftAIBoilerplatePro:\\n\\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj`\\n- `Config/App.xcconfig`\\n- `Packages/Core`\\n- `Packages/Networking`\\n- `Packages/Storage`\\n- `Packages/Auth`\\n- `Packages/Payments`\\n- `Packages/AI`\\n- `Packages/FeatureSettings`\\n- `Packages/Localization`\\n- `Packages/DesignSystem`\\n- `CompositionRoot`\\n\\nIf any module is removed, the ADR must explain dependency order and App Store 4.3 consequences.\\n\\nIMPLEMENT_INTEGRATION:\\n# Implement Integration Phase\\n\\nImplement only the integration and release-hardening phase in `{{ inputs.app_dir|default(\\\"apps/generated-iphone-app\\\") }}`.\\n\\nScope:\\n\\n- wire feature into CompositionRoot/AppShell\\n- complete tests and UI test fixtures\\n- complete `scripts/ci/ios-quality.sh`\\n- complete `.github/workflows/ios-quality.yml`\\n- complete Appium exploratory script\\n- generate `reports/ios/ios-quality-report.json` when quality checks pass\\n- generate `reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json` when Appium checks pass\\n- create release/readiness docs\\n\\nThe CI script must include xcodebuild build/test, SwiftLint, SwiftFormat, Qlty, secret scan, and App Store string audit.\\n\\nSecret handling is blocking: never print environment variables or credential values. CI and local scripts may verify that required secrets are present, but output must be redacted true/false status only.\\n\\nWrite `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evidence/integration.md` with:\\n\\n- `Files changed`\\n- `Commands run`\\n- `Acceptance criteria`\\n- `Risks`\\n\\nAI_UI_EXPLORER:\\n# AI UI Explorer\\n\\nRun or complete the automated exploratory UI pass for `{{ inputs.app_dir|default(\\\"apps/generated-iphone-app\\\") }}`.\\n\\nThe target behavior is: launch the iOS app in simulator through Appium/XCUITest and tap every reachable enabled button/control across the MVP flows.\\n\\nThe explorer should:\\n\\n- record each screen source or screenshot\\n- identify buttons, tabs, cells, navigation controls, and primary actions\\n- tap controls breadth-first with a bounded depth\\n- recover with back/navigation when possible\\n- detect crashes, blank screens, stuck spinners, and unhandled error screens\\n- produce `reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json`\\n\\nThe report JSON must include:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"ok\\\": true,\\n  \\\"buttons_tapped\\\": 0,\\n  \\\"screens_visited\\\": 0,\\n  \\\"crashes\\\": 0,\\n  \\\"failures\\\": 0,\\n  \\\"failures_detail\\\": []\\n}\\n```\\n\\nDo not mark the pass complete unless a real simulator/Appium run happened, unless the workflow explicitly allows macOS deferral.\\n\\nFINAL_CONSENSUS:\\n# Final Consensus Review\\n\\nRead:\\n\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/product-fidelity.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/ios-architecture.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/security-privacy.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/code-quality.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/release-readiness.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/qa-evidence.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/quality-contract-gate.json`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/ios-ci-gate.json`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/appium-gate.json`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/app-store-hardening-gate.json`\\n\\nMerge the review fanout into a final release decision.\\n\\nRules:\\n\\n- If any reviewer finds a blocking issue, reject.\\n- If macOS/Xcode or Appium evidence is missing and not explicitly deferred, reject.\\n- If the app does not use the boilerplate substantially, reject.\\n- If App Store 4.3 hardening did not pass, reject.\\n\\nWrite `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/final-consensus.md` with:\\n\\n- reviewer agreement/disagreement\\n- blocking issues\\n- remaining deferred items\\n- release handoff notes\\n\\nEnd with exactly one verdict line:\\n\\n`VERDICT: APPROVED`\\n\\nor\\n\\n`VERDICT: REJECTED`\\n\\nReturn valid JSON only, no markdown fences:\\n{\\\"verdict\\\":\\\"APPROVE\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.0,\\\"covered\\\":[\\\"spec_lab\\\",\\\"boilerplate_reuse\\\",\\\"ios_quality\\\",\\\"appium_qa\\\",\\\"mobbin_safety\\\",\\\"release_hardening\\\"],\\\"gaps\\\":[]}\\n\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:118:          \"label\": \"Evaluate whether this iPhone App Factory prompt suite is strong enough for overnight agentic app generation.\\n\\nPrompt registry:\\n{{prompt_registry}}\\n\\nGolden cases:\\n{{golden_cases}}\\n\\nRepresentative prompts:\\nSPEC_CONSENSUS:\\n{{spec_consensus}}\\n\\nARCHITECTURE:\\n{{architecture_consensus}}\\n\\nIMPLEMENT_INTEGRATION:\\n{{implement_integration}}\\n\\nAI_UI_EXPLORER:\\n{{ai_ui_explorer}}\\n\\nFINAL_CONSENSUS:\\n{{final_consensus}}\\n\\nReturn valid JSON only, no markdown fences:\\n{\\\"verdict\\\":\\\"APPROVE\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.0,\\\"covered\\\":[\\\"spec_lab\\\",\\\"boilerplate_reuse\\\",\\\"ios_quality\\\",\\\"appium_qa\\\",\\\"mobbin_safety\\\",\\\"release_hardening\\\"],\\\"gaps\\\":[]}\\n\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:150:        \"score\": 0,\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:249:      \"Evaluate whether this iPhone App Factory prompt suite is strong enough for overnight agentic app generation.\\n\\nPrompt registry:\\n{{prompt_registry}}\\n\\nGolden cases:\\n{{golden_cases}}\\n\\nRepresentative prompts:\\nSPEC_CONSENSUS:\\n{{spec_consensus}}\\n\\nARCHITECTURE:\\n{{architecture_consensus}}\\n\\nIMPLEMENT_INTEGRATION:\\n{{implement_integration}}\\n\\nAI_UI_EXPLORER:\\n{{ai_ui_explorer}}\\n\\nFINAL_CONSENSUS:\\n{{final_consensus}}\\n\\nReturn valid JSON only, no markdown fences:\\n{\\\"verdict\\\":\\\"APPROVE\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.0,\\\"covered\\\":[\\\"spec_lab\\\",\\\"boilerplate_reuse\\\",\\\"ios_quality\\\",\\\"appium_qa\\\",\\\"mobbin_safety\\\",\\\"release_hardening\\\"],\\\"gaps\\\":[]}\\n\"\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/context.md:3:App: WakeTask\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/context.md:4:Bundle ID: com.keen.waketask\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/context.md:5:Output: apps/waketask-iphone\n.workflow/iphone-app-fac