mpetitors.md:16:### 1) Alarmy - Loud alarm clock\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research/competitors.md:17:- Link: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/alarmy-loud-alarm-clock/id1163786766\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_6","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' .workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md\"","aggregated_output":"# WakeTask Architecture\n\n## Purpose\nBuild WakeTask as an extension of `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro` with no foundational rewrites, preserving strict Swift 6 concurrency, CI quality gates, and App Store differentiation through the two-phase wake model.\n\n## System Topology\n1. `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj` remains the integration shell and target graph owner.\n2. `CompositionRoot` wires app services, repositories, and feature routes into the app scene.\n3. Feature packages implement WakeTask domain flows behind protocol boundaries owned by `Packages/Core`.\n4. iOS app target and UI tests validate end-to-end alarm, mission, fallback, and wake-check flows.\n\n## Boilerplate Module Mapping\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj`\n  - Keep as root project; add WakeTask feature targets/schemes only as needed.\n- `Config/App.xcconfig`\n  - Keep as source of bundle id/environment toggles (`com.keen.waketask`) and build flags.\n- `Packages/Core`\n  - Owns domain models/protocols for alarms, mission chain, wake-check schedule, reliability timeline, and context profile selection.\n- `Packages/Networking`\n  - Reused for remote config/pricing copy fetches and optional telemetry upload; no alarm-critical behavior depends on network availability.\n- `Packages/Storage`\n  - Persists per-alarm reliability telemetry fields (`alarm_scheduled_at`, `alarm_fired_at`, `dismissed_at`, `wake_check_results`, `fallback_used`, `profile_used`) and mission/profile configuration.\n- `Packages/Auth`\n  - Retained unchanged for account/session if enabled; wake-critical execution remains functional without blocking on auth.\n- `Packages/Payments`\n  - Retained for transparent paywall and entitlement checks; monetization messaging kept outside alarm-critical interaction steps.\n- `Packages/AI`\n  - Retained for non-critical assistant/personalization surfaces only; never required for alarm firing, dismissal, fallback, or wake verification.\n- `Packages/FeatureSettings`\n  - Hosts alarm defaults, strictness profiles (weekday/weekend/travel), permission recovery affordances, and tone/policy options.\n- `Packages/Localization`\n  - Owns all user-facing strings, including App Store 4.3 differentiation language and anti-\"guaranteed wake\" constraints.\n- `Packages/DesignSystem`\n  - Implements 3:30am-safe components (large targets, high contrast, low cognitive load), avoiding ad-like clutter.\n- `CompositionRoot`\n  - Registers implementations for mission engine, fallback resolver, wake-check scheduler, reliability logger, and screen entry points.\n\n## WakeTask Feature Slices\n1. Alarm Setup Slice\n- Configure alarm + mission chain.\n- Validate mission inputs at setup (scan target pre-validation, camera permission checks).\n\n2. Alarm Execution Slice\n- Fire alarm locally.\n- Enforce mission-gated dismissal (math, memory, motion, scan).\n- Route to fallback mission in one step on unavailable/invalid primary mission conditions.\n\n3. Post-dismiss Verification Slice\n- Schedule wake checks at +3, +7, +12 minutes from dismissal time.\n- Escalate via re-alarm on missed/failed checks.\n- Mark session successful only if all required checks pass.\n\n4. Trust & Review Slice\n- Render morning timeline from persisted reliability fields.\n- Expose fallback usage and profile used for trust transparency.\n\n## Dependency Direction\n1. `DesignSystem`/`Localization` are leaf presentation dependencies.\n2. `FeatureSettings` and WakeTask feature UIs depend on `Core` protocols and DesignSystem.\n3. Repository implementations depend on `Storage` and optionally `Networking`.\n4. Monetization/auth adapters depend on `Payments`/`Auth` but never invert into `Core`.\n5. `CompositionRoot` performs final assembly and injects protocols into app entry points.\n\n## Concurrency and Reliability Constraints\n- Isolate alarm-state mutation behind actor-backed services.\n- Use main-actor view models and async protocol APIs for mission evaluation and wake checks.\n- Keep mission and wake-check scheduling deterministic and resumable after app relaunch.\n- Ensure fallback routing cannot dead-end by requiring an always-available fallback mission type.\n\n## Testing and Evidence Plan\n- Unit tests: mission validators, fallback resolver, wake-check scheduler timing, reliability timeline mapping.\n- Integration tests: full dismissal->wake-check escalation path and permission denial recovery.\n- UI tests/Appium exploratory: tap every reachable enabled control, include trust log/profile switching routes.\n- Blocking quality gates: `xcodebuild build`, `xcodebuild test`, SwiftLint, SwiftFormat, Qlty, secret scan, App Store string audit.\n\n## Non-goals Guardrail\n- No rebuild of Auth/Payments/AI/Networking/Storage/Localization/DesignSystem/CompositionRoot.\n- No sleep-stage analytics platform, social wake community, or wearable-required core logic in MVP.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
